    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-04-07T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-04-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="634"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d634">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/1069.</note>
                <head>[Untitled]</head>
                <p>Referring to the memorandum of the 20th ultimo, in which the Embassy of Mexico
                    stated that the authorities at Del Rio had stopped a shipment of arms and
                    ammunition intended for Mexican insurgents, the Department of State has the
                    honor to say that, it is informed by the Attorney General, in a letter dated
                    March 25, 1911, that he is bringing the case to the attention of the appropriate
                    United States attorney and is instructing him to investigate the matter and to
                    take such proceedings in the premises as may be warranted by law.</p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-04-07">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 7, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
